// TEST: exec_core_time_duration
// EXPECT: output "2500;1500;1500;60;-60000000000"
// EXPECT: targets js, ts, python, rust, go
//
// Cross-target proof that the §18.3.1 `Duration` surface — the builtin span type
// stored as signed nanoseconds — constructs, does arithmetic, and reports its
// components identically on every target. `Duration`, its constructors, methods,
// and `+`/`-`/`*` operators are compiler builtins (registered in `bock-core`'s
// primitive registry and lowered inline by every backend), NOT a `core.*` Bock
// module — so this fixture exercises the prelude-builtin `Duration` directly,
// with no `use`.
//
// The five printed fields are integer-only on every target (Python `/` is float
// division, so `Duration / Int` and `Bool` interpolation are deliberately
// avoided — see exec_iter_combinators.bock for the same integer-only discipline):
//   * sum     = 2s + 500ms                  -> as_millis() == 2500
//   * diff    = 2s - 500ms                  -> as_millis() == 1500
//   * scaled  = 500ms * 3                    -> as_millis() == 1500
//   * absd    = (0 - 1min).abs()            -> as_seconds() == 60
//   * neg     = 0 - 1min                     -> as_nanos()  == -60000000000
// => "2500;1500;1500;60;-60000000000". This exercises the `seconds`/`millis`/
// `minutes`/`zero` constructors, the `+`/`-`/`*` operator overloads, `abs`, and
// the `as_millis`/`as_seconds`/`as_nanos` accessors — the deterministic subset of
// §18.3.1. `Instant`/`now`/`sleep` are intentionally excluded: they read the host
// monotonic clock and are non-deterministic (and shim-gated), so they cannot have
// a fixed expected output.
//
// `main` is intentionally NOT `public` (see hello_world.bock for the Go
// entry-point rationale).
module main

fn main() -> Void {
  let a = Duration.seconds(2)
  let b = Duration.millis(500)
  let sum = a + b
  let diff = a - b
  let scaled = b * 3
  let neg = Duration.zero() - Duration.minutes(1)
  let absd = neg.abs()
  println("${sum.as_millis()};${diff.as_millis()};${scaled.as_millis()};${absd.as_seconds()};${neg.as_nanos()}")
}
